Title : Wishart Peninsula
Text : The '''Wishart Peninsula''' is a [[peninsula]] on the [[British Columbia Coast|Coast of British Columbia]], located east of [[Broughton Island (British Columbia)|Broughton Island]] to the south of [[Wakeman Sound]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/25543.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Wishart Peninsula"]</ref>

==Name origin==
The peninsula and [[Wishart Island (British Columbia)]] in the [[Deserters Group]] are named for a James Wishart, who was one of the crew of the [[Hudson's Bay Company|HBC]] vessel [[Norman Morrison (ship)|''Norman Morrison'']] who deserted that vessel and were killed on the Deserters Group islands by natives sent out to find and capture them.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/25494.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Deserters Island"]</ref>

